Description.en-us: Configure modified behavior in the Edit-UI

EditInstructions.en-us: This adjusts some features of the edit UI. It is still beta, so anything you do here may change in future.

Notes.en-us: Mark something in the system to be part of an export set.

DropdownValues.en-us:
:Default Crop - Use image as the template expects it, usually crop to center
none:Don't Crop - the entire image should be visible
to:Corner or Side Crop - the most important part is in a corner or on a side

:🎯 Default - Center
tl:↖️ Top Left
tc:⬆️ Top Center
tr:↗️ Top Right
ml:⬅️ Middle Left
mc:🎯 Middle Center
mr:➡️ Middle Right
bl:↙️ Bottom Left

Notes.en-us: Important: Crop settings will only take effect if the template creating the HTML interprets the settings. If it seems like the settings don't work, please contact your web developer.
Notes.de-de: Wichtig: Zuschnittseinstellungen haben nur einen Effekt, wenn der Template-Code (der Teil, welches HTML generiert) diese Einstellungen auch berücksichtigt. Sollten deine Anpassungen nicht den erwünschten Effekt haben, frag bitte deinen Webdesigner.

EditInstructions.en-us: Give your image some alternate text for screen readers and configure how it should be resized.
EditInstructions.de-de: Gib deinem Bild eine Alternativbeschreibung (für Google und für Menschen mit Behinderungen). Du kannst auch steuern, wie das Bild automatisch zugeschnitten wird.

Description.en-us: Configure what Metadata is expected on something

EditInstructions.en-us:
This configures what Metadata is expected on this kind of item. It's mainly used to help create toolbars automatically. 

Important: This wil not prevent other metadata, but simply make work easier.

Description.en-us: Mark a Content-Type to allow empty-items to be saved.

EditInstructions.en-us:
By default, content-types without fields would result in empty items, and they would not be saved. 

Use this decorator to mark a content-type which should save items even if they are completely empty.
